title: BLM Wilderness Study Areas for the State of Colorado (Polygon)
name: BLM Wilderness Study Areas for the State of Colorado (Polygon)
description:
Draft Resource Management Plan and Environmental Impact Statement, published December 2012
This data set consist of digital data describing (WSA) Wilderness Study Area Boundaries for the State
of Colorado. The data set includes 1:24,000 wsa maps for the four BLM Districts in Colorado: Grand
Junction, Craig, Canon City, and Montrose. Data originally digitized using ArcEdit. Data set is
projected into UTM zone 13. Individual coverages were merged into a single coverage. The file was
checked for polygon topology, dangles, and slivers. Any errors of this kind were corrected before
creating the E00 ArcInfo interchange file. A portion of the Sewemup WSA is outside the GJFO planning area (within UFO) and is not included in analysis or this dataset. 

For more information on the BLM standard/metadata refer to Instruction
Bulletin 99-210 located at:

<URL:http://www.fgdc.gov/Metadata/Metadata.html>
